nts1.d:
Three Blind Mice is a jazz label set up by producer Takeshi Fujii in 1970. The label focused on Japanese jazz artists, and it's often called the Japanese Blue Note. It was renowned for the quality of its recordings (most of which were recorded by engineer Yoshihiko Kannari), and its incredible artwork. 
In this third episode of our Japanese Jazz Week series, we’ll hear many of the label’s artists, including Isao Suzki, Kosuke Mine, & Masaru Imada.

nts1.n: NTS Guide to: Rare Groove Inspired Jungle
nts1.d:

The foundational bedrock of the genre – the break – are isolated drum sections from older records, most notably the break from The Winstons' "Amen Brother". This re-imagining of classic soul, jazz and R&B music often extends to the melodic samples in jungle, creating a distinctive softer side to the genre, recalling slow jams and emotive ballads.

Bolero was once termed the 'quintessential Latin American romantic song of the twentieth century', a Cuban genre originating in the late 19th century out of the trova tradition, pioneered by troubadour Pepe Sánchez. Boleros are defined by their love-themed lyrics, but musically can take a variety of forms; as such it has such been fused with a variety of other genres over time such as rumba, mambo, and chachachá - giving the genre such an enduring and timeless quality.
The boleros were originally sung by single trovadores playing guitar, but it soon became popular for trovadores to play in groups as dúos, tríos, cuartetos. After gaining global popularity, boleros paved the way for the filin movement in Havana - a word derived from feeling, describing a style of post-microphone jazz-influenced romantic song.
This Guide To covers the most romantic exitos of the genres bolero and filin, crooners for the month of love.

nts1.d: The beloved collective and club night HE4RTBROKEN is celebrating its 10th anniversary. They will celebrate their 10 years birthday on 14th February at Brussels' iconic venue Ancienne Belgique with a stacked line-up including Smerz, Dj Python, Why Be, Golin and SKY H1.

Tearooms in post-revolution Czechoslovakia symbolised places through which new spiritualities were flowing, and the influx of largely uncharted ways of life closely intertwined with new age, ambient, folk and minimalism. With their minds altered thanks to smuggled records by Fripp & Eno or Steve Reich, this loose network of musicians had begun composing meditative music, using loops and handmade instruments, with a different sensibility. Compared to the boisterous Zappa-adjacent and booze-soaked underground movement, which was led by Plastic People of the Universe and provoked the state authorities, this music was meant instead for tea rooms and spiritual sites like churches or monasteries, as if occupying some place where time flows anticlockwise. Music journalist Pavel Klusák dubbed this 1990s scene a “tearoom alternative”. Experimental folk singer Oldřich Janota, Jaroslav Kořán’s various ensembles like Modrá or Orloj Snivců (The Horologe of Dreamers) or Irena and Vojtěch Havlovi were drawn by the light and composed music that didn’t match the fast pace of newly imported capitalism.

Based in Cotonou, Benin, which at the time was referred to as Dahomey, Albarika Records was founded by the French-born, Benin-based producer and entrepreneur, Emmanuel "Manu" Dibango, who had a significant influence on the local music scene. The label was instrumental in releasing records from some of the region's most prominent musicians during the golden age of African music.
Many of the artists signed to Albarika Records were known for blending indigenous African rhythms with Western jazz, funk, and soul influences. This made their sound distinctive and part of a broader movement across West Africa during the 60s and 70s, as music became a form of social and political expression.

nts1.n: IN FOCUS: EMAHOY TSEGE MARIAM GEBRU (R)
nts1.d:
An hour of spellbinding solo piano recordings from one of the most fascinating musicians of the past century. Born Yewubdar Guèbrou in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia, into an upper class family, she was classically trained in piano and violin, notably even performing for Emperor Haile Selassie. 
She was invited to study at the Royal College of Music in London, but her admission was blocked by the Ethiopian government. Dismayed by this news, she turned to religion, becoming an Orthodox nun, taking the title "Emahoy" and changing to the religious name Tsegué Mariam.
She spent the rest of her years living out these holy orders, first in Addis, and eventually in Jerusalem, where she continued to write and record music – a truly singular style of piano composition, as indebted to the proto-ambience of Erik Satie as it is to the Ethiopian tradition.

Popol Vuh – the musical collective founded by German keyboardist Florian Fricke – is inseperable from Fricke himself. The spiritual engine of the project, Fricke was a true citizen of the world, well travelled and resolutely open minded, absorbing new cultures, spiritualities, and most importantly music with studious interest. 
Fricke accquired one of the first Moog II synthesisers in Europe in 1969, and thus Popol Vuh began as a pioneering electronic music act. Eventually Fricke and his collective abandoned electronic for expansive accoustic arrangements inspired by pre-Colombian American music, Tibetan music, African music and beyond, often working in tandem with another singular German auteur – filmmaker Werner Herzog.

nts2.n: AN IBEX BAND SPECIAL: THE ROHA BAND YEARS (R)
nts2.d:
The legendary Ibex Band - later known as the iconic Roha Band - played a key role in shaping Ethiopian music from the mid-1970s onward. Though hugely influential, their legacy remains underrecognised. In this special episode, NTS presents a two hour deep dive into their catalogue, tracing their evolution and showcasing rare, overlooked tracks from their archive. Join us as we celebrate the musicians behind the music and explore their lasting cultural impact. 
Special thanks to John Henriksson, Johan Egerbladh Eurenius, Muzikawi and Zuret Addis.

nts2.n: ALICE COLTRANE SPECIAL: TRANSCENDING THROUGH MUSIC (R)
nts2.d:
In the immediate years following her husband's death, Alice Coltrane underwent a challenging personal journey, finally emerging from emotional turmoil when she was introduced to guru Swami Satchidananda in the early 1970s. By 1972 she had changed her name to Turiyasangitananda, and left her secular life behind, moving to California. In 1975, she opened the Vedantic Centre.This spiritual awakening would define much of the rest of her life, her music notwithstanding. 
This show explores Alice's later recordings, which are deeply influenced by Hinduism and Eastern spirituality, featuring bhajan chants, and new age influence.
Artist, filmmaker, and DJ Ephraim Asili, pays tribute to Alice Coltrane, exploring her legacy via the work presented in the exhibition, 'Alice Coltrane, Monument Eternal' at The Hammer Museum.

When visionary electronic producer SOPHIE passed away in 2021 aged only 34, it felt like the extinguishing of a future path for music, the one down which she was lighting the way. Few musicians in 21st Century have diffused their influence throughout pop music and beyond as inexorably as SOPHIE. 
She created sounds that tore music – and by extension her own identity – down to its molecular constituents, alchemising them to thrilling effect, in a way that spellbound both the avant-garde and the poptimists alike. Since her passing, her devoted fanbase remains as active as ever, cataloging and archive SOPHIE's vast discography of officially and unofficially released music.

nts2.n: watch my mum dance w/ bbymix
nts2.d:
Peace for me feels like spring: hilltop at sunrise, bathing in soundscapes of the wind. A feeling a daybreak after the storm that begins with silence, encompassing the storm as well as the calm. Like what a baby hears: pure, before the world imposes. 
In the first track, the dialogue tells the perspective of the baby before birth. In the womb, we cannot see, touch, smell, taste—but we can hear. This our first instance of peace, and we unlearn individually and collectively, to get back to that presence.

How words and music can heal a heart and let us be carried by the wind, through the sound of a flute, an electric guitar riff, or powerful soul voices. 
This mix is composed of sounds that have been bringing peace or grounding, at different times of my life, somehow bringing a feeling of an in-between the earth and the sky, going from heaviness to heaven, alchemizing grief into jasmines, growing butterfly wings. The selection present different genres but I tried to build a journey that could bring joy, calmness, and high vibrations (selection was hard!) In this sea of words pronounced by the different artists, or told by the various instruments that are playing, I added some words from Maya Angelou and from my heart.

For me, peace is synonymous with home — a corner of the world that we carve out and enrich with every facet of our identity. Here I offer up a set of tracks to play when you want to feel the walls pulsing with sweet, sweet soul.

nts2.n: Where Earth Meets Sky w/ Chi-Chi Usagi
nts2.d: I’m coming out from two of the toughest years of my life, and the music you are about to hear is what saved me. This mix features the song I walked down the aisle to at my wedding a few months before my life was flipped upside down, songs that held me through lonely nights dealing with withdrawals from an addiction I’d held onto for 10 years, songs that comforted me when I was kicked out of my career, songs that I danced on the roof to in the rain during the last nights in my home, Brooklyn, NY. All of this music has held me through moments that tested my willpower. The love that I have for myself and the love that I have for God is what got me through it all. May this little snippet of my peace touch something within you.

nts2.n: Regions of Peace w/ steven seven seven

A mix that embraces music from different regions of the world, where the memories held within each song bring me joy and, eventually, peace. These are sounds from diverse eras and places that might have never met in time, yet here they coexist in harmony.
Organic and electronic textures blend with emotional energy: they exalt intensity but also honor silence. Speed and stillness converge into a fluid harmony that invites reflection, memory, and breath.
Peace is not a moment,  it’s a continuous presence. It should be lived from every place, in every time, and remembered and desired always.

黃美琦 vicki huang / 鹽埕區長salt district mayor
靜不下的歌 music for movements is a hybrid vinyl-CD mix recorded live at 潮電 Chao Bar&RecordStore in Taipei. Presented by 鹽埕區長 Salt District Mayor — an audiovisual archive and label devoted to Taiwanese roots music — the mix was originally recorded for my monthly Taiwanese Music History Book Club at Chao Bar. Our September session explored Jeph Lo’s ALTERing NATIVism: Sound Cultures in Post-War Taiwan, and I was especially moved by the chapter on banned songs.
This set gathers those silenced voices — from banned songs and protest anthems to ballads of belonging and hope — tracing Taiwan’s long tradition of using music as a tool for social change. Across Mandarin, Taiwanese Hokkien, and Hakka languages, the mix journeys from campus-folk awakenings and labor anthems to Indigenous blues and anti-nuclear protest songs. Each record is a reminder that peace is not the absence of noise, but the courage to keep singing.
Note: The live mix recorded at Chao Bar was around 40min, so I added a few more tracks digitized from my vinyl collection to extend the mix to an hour length. The Chao Bar mix was also taped on video, so if interested, I could cut a few clips for NTS Radio to share on instagram. Thank you for your time and this opportunity!

Something happened to me this past summer… I encountered the peaceful bliss that is the music of Exotica for the first time. I become so fixated on its relaxing and hypnotic beauty that it became this paradise of sound that I returned to again and again.
In the late 1950’s, Martin Denny ditched his orchestral, Big Band sound to create what would be known as the “Exotica” genre. Combining the music of lounge jazz with tropical flavors from the Hawaiian & Caribbean islands, he birthed something uniquely experiential for its time. While it was despised by critics during its era, it became a hit within tiki bars and beach side resorts, it later brought about a cult following. Other artists in Denny’s circle joined and made it in their own vision. With the sounds of bird calls, animals howling, and ocean waves crashing, you get a cinematic experience with every song. This mix is a curated journey through this forgotten time in music. Welcome back to paradise.

nts2.d: Tranquil soundscapes and fuzzy tones. The dichotomy of sound is proof that peace is something found at home.

quiet moments, bliss, ease, memory
showing gratitude for the little things and keeping in mind that theres still a chance for peace. some things are worth fighting for! gotta remember that. these songs make me keep going.

nts2.n: WHEN THE SKY WAS WHOLE W/ SLUMP
nts2.d: Slower jams and B-Sides. Sauntering across the landscape.

Everyone knows peace when they feel it: harmony, tranquility, love. But getting there can take work. That means care and respect for others, a lot of fearlessness, even some self-sacrifice. Done right, though, it’s a labor of joy. Because all life is precious (ignore the haters), and because together we will win.

nts2.n: The weight of dust w/ auds
nts2.d:
The afternoon sun soaks up the remaining moody puddles
the corner of her mouth starts to gleam
Grandma turns on her dusty jukebox stereo -
Then,
Her chest flutters to space.

Recorded in the effortless charm of a peaceful lil garden in Taormina, Sicily. With my grandma. 
Recalling the following; the lovely Ionian Sea staring up at me. The ocean looking so still, gleaming with sweet sparkles.
I’m looking forward though, to sitting on my warm front porch back home, and letting my heart flutter to space !
I hope these songs can make your heart flutter too.
Lots of love 
Audrey <3

The freedom to dance, wander or be still. To be reminded of home, loved
ones and moments of true calm. These songs were listened to with a cat on
my lap, on a walk in the sun, sitting at the park and looking at ducks.
Peace comes from within but I hope this mix meets you on the way there.

Peace is indeed can be found anywhere if we search for it although sometimes it seems a bit impossible for the world so in this mix the search is for inner peace with a touch of sadness and joy through jazz, ambient, some folky guitar tunes… 
It's a journey from a muslim saying, a wish for peace in the first sense of the word for which we crave a lot, to a more vague meaning of peace… 
Hope we find it, alone and all together…

A one take vinyl only mix. This is a lil introspective journey through some of my most personal and intimate records. Songs and artists that, in the natural chaos of life, would ground me. Soul nourishers. Anxiety relievers. 
The image of the cows in a field was taken by me in Armenia this October, where the infinite landscapes resonated with sound waves going through the most serene empty valleys. 
Raw Kernels is a series of vinyl-only mixes that express the complexities of human vulnerabilities. A space where I encourage myself and others to share little delicate, painful, hidden, perhaps even forgotten pieces of themselves, play records that we usually don't have the chance to, due to some social pressure or setting. It is genre defying, complex and cathartic. Raw Kernels focuses on expressing heartfelt connection with music through playful and intricate mixing. My own oasis. 
I hope to transmit a feeling of peace through this medium. I hope you feel it. It's not perfect, it's raw! From TwoFace's lil room with Love. Thank you for listening. :)

nts2.n: We Sing Together to Keep Ourselves Warm W/ Splendore
nts2.d: Modern and sacred choirs, recorded in small villages and grand places of worship. When we choose to sing, we do it to keep warm, to protect one another, to love

A quiet search for peace — within and beyond ourselves. I find it in the sax of Jeff Jones, guitars drifting through other worlds, in Talos’ ethereal voice, in thunder and crickets recorded by Kokubo Takashi — moments where inner peace softly echoes outward, gently stirring change.

nts2.n: SERENITY IN REFLECTION W/ PEACEKEEPER RADIO
nts2.d: A reflection on PEACEKEEPER RADIO, a peace-themed mix series I've run for the past three years. Featuring tracks from past collaborators alongside songs that offered clarity in creative uncertainty, it explores how peace emerges through stillness, shared sound and collective practice.

This mix is my auditory representation of the afterlife - a place where one finds true peace. Including ethereal voices, dreamy pads and long, layered ambient tracks, enjoy this dreamlike recording where familiarity and weirdness and everyday logic does not apply.
an attempt at a playlist for and about peace—an offering, as it so often is; not merely an absence of war, but a possibility, a very personal proposition, something that can also hold power, softly.

“Mentors are everywhere”, I thought while chatting to a taxi driver many years ago. In the quest for peace with yourself, music acts as a channel to emotions, wisdom and discoveries. In some weird way, music is that never-ending depository of mentors. This mixtape is a directional journey across high and lows and ultimately, acceptance and hope.

There’s a kind of stillness that appears suddenly, like a flash revealing what I had overlooked. As soon as I reach it, it seems to dissolve, yet it keeps shaping the way I listen to the world. In that space where time loosens and sounds lose their names, I looked for a calm that wasn’t escape but presence. This mix was born after a period of relentless noise, when I rediscovered the relief of silence and the gratitude for every fragment of peace regained.
Quiet nostalgia and gentle mise-en-scène curated by a film obsessed curtain maker.

rebajada for dawn is a tribute to the darkness into light hour; time spent brewing tea before the world and its actions seep into the day, slowed down but woven for immediacy and variation, peace and energy

nts2.n: PEACE PIECE W/ SOFIA DE AFRICA
nts2.d: Listen in peace: A slow drift toward quiet. Music for soft focus, open skies, and the calm after everything.

nts2.n: REST IN PEACE W/ SIDHARTTA TALUKDAR
nts2.d:
Funeral songs, dirges, chants, fugues and laments for the dead. Researched and compiled by Chakma sound artist Sidhartta Talukdar.
Photo by Krisna Yuda on Unsplash.

Insomnia is a place, a peaceful castle. By 3am, the world softens into a fragile quiet, like writing in a diary when no one is watching. And from time to time, unexpected companions stir, daring to reveal the secret worlds they carry within.
Tracing peace through deeply intimate vocal, ambient and classical works. "I’m bathing in soft air, wrapping around every inch of my skin like a warm hug."

nts2.n: Smultronstället w/ Adviser on Shade Trees
nts2.d: It is amazing how full a life a man can lead without for one moment being alive at all, except sometimes when sleeping. —Robert Aickman

To me, peace is uplifting my community. I resonate with those who also exhibit alterity- queer people, women, and people of color. This is a collection of artists from that community, without labels- the purest form of showing up, as you are, in peace.

nts2.n: Explosive Flesh w/ DJ Obsessive Fantasy
WRETCHED OF THE EARTH W/ ECHODRIS
nts2.d: Ain't no peace till there's peace in Gaza. A dark night of the soul through loss in a time of crisis and reckoning. Mix title borrowed from the book "Wretched of the Earth" by Frantz Fanon.

nts2.n: Void Anomalies w/ Harsh Noise Boyfriend
nts2.d:
[dis]comfort in empty corners. 
tracing creases of an uneasy peace.
smells like cemetery,
late autumn.

You are lying on a soft pink cloud while the sun pokes from behind the earth beneath. There is no wind and no sound. The sky and everything around you slowly changes colors until the sun has finally risen.

nts2.n: EVERYDAY A FEELING W/ SPELLS FOR NATURE
nts2.d: everyday a feeling is an hour of meditative & spacious sounds for quiet nights at home.

If I can pause long enough to light an incense, I know I'm going to be okay. It’s the only 5-second ritual I have that immediately grounds me. The smoke always clears something up. These songs embody that feeling. I play them on loop when I need comfort. They always clear something up. Always.

This mix is a collection of lush, deep and blissed out ambient jungle tracks from the late 90s - gorgeously thick and otherwordly atmospheres paired with rolling breaks, ideal for gazing over and melting into serene natural landscapes and letting your mind wander

nts2.n: making a desert and calling it peace w/ Shivanayama
nts2.d: it is an endless and often restless search for peace
Remote Dreaming is for the ones who dream out loud in empty rooms. A distant lullaby for close strangers and slow dancers.

nts2.n: BETWEEN TREES AND OISEAUX W/ NUMA
nts2.d: A calm drift through raw edges and open space — quiet sparks, deep breath, peace of mind in motion.

The sounds of peace are the quiet sounds of domesticity - objects moving in space, half-utterances, fragments of melody. Brief glimpses of beauty. A few throughlines: 00s glitch and folktronica, spoken word, field recordings.
Fragments of serenity to gently soothe the chaos.
back home from the party thinking "man I love this place"

Ciao sono santapazienza, una ricercatrice accanita di musica di ogni genere ma non comune. Attualmente vivo a Torino e ho 25 anni.
Ho preparato questo set prima di andare a dormire, per fare bei sogni.

Hi everyone, I think it’s very hard not to get distracted with everything demanding our attention. Now more than ever, we’ve got to take back our time and attention to focus on what’s important. I’ve started collecting songs that bring me peace in troubled times. May it help you too <3

This set is inspired by 90s liquid jungle. I find this music one very effective way to calm my mind in times where war, warcrimes, cruelty, injustice and fear are on display. 
I hope this mix has the same effect for the listeners. even though it may seem hard, and in this injustice, for some it is impossible because they struggle to survive, I still think its important to remember that we are capable of making and enjoying beautiful and meaningful art. and that it can make us come together.

nts2.n: AGE OF CONCORD AND REPOSE W/ ALONSO FLORES
nts2.d: Stillness drifts as tenderness echoes and aches; songs for quiet reflection and unanchored listening, live from Copenhagen.
Home is peace — an ambient journey through migration, memory, and return. A sound collection of shared memories and distant places, like an albatross crossing the sea, finding calm in echoes of home

It’s beautiful to feel how everything is connected.
You just have to listen closely,
and you can hear how the eternal thread stretches on,
binding everything together — you, me, Lonnie Holley and Alice Coltrane. Join me on this trip to inner peace.

nts2.n: Waves of Peace w/ Jaxx TMS
nts2.d: For this mix I chose a selection that takes me to a place of peace, a state where im not thinking, just being.Everything else fades away. You are fully present, almost meditative. I wanted to create a space to breathe, listen and float. Sounds that move through us so we can be carried by their melodies. Creating this felt completely naturally, almost effortlessly, it resonates so deeply with me to my own stillness.

My dad has always played the guitar, and this collection of music revolves around his favorite instrument. From classic folk tales to droning harmonics, I trace the path of finding one's own self-sustainment and peace of mind through sonic meditation.
Image: untitled drawing by my dad, 1974.

i feel most at peace when i’m outside, taking in the beauty of nature and things around me. this mix channels that feeling of inner peace - so grab your headphones and go outside!
may we all be able to experience this feeling <3

nts2.n: I AM A PART OF THE ROAD W/ CAROLINE RAYNER
nts2.d: The sound of driving all day when you’ve got a long way to go and it's just you and the sky and the light as it changes.
“Peace comes when realizing the love you lost was not for you”… taken from the doo wop diary of a sad ass foo </3

nts2.n: PEACE TOGETHER THE PIECES W/ M. SHAAR & NINA G.
RADIO SUPER W/ ROSA PISTOLA - TRIBAL MEXICANO VOLUMEN I (R)
nts2.d: RADIO SUPER is Rosa Pistola’s show on NTS where she dives deep into the Latin American underground. Each episode zooms into different genres, scenes, and vibes, tracing their roots and evolution. It’s all about the sounds, the stories, and the pillars of the underground.

nts2.n: CDMX TAPES W/ TEZCATLIPOCA SOUNDSISTEMA & ADAKEO (R)
nts2.d: Mexican record label, Naafi, settle in at NTS for a showcase of the weirdest experimentations in club culture that have bubbled to the surface of Soundcloud. Dazed rhythms converging into Jersey stutters, and tumblr-era trap for two straight hours on a Monday.
DJ, Run Dem Crew Founder, and community builder Charlie Dark MBE spins gems from his record collection once a month.

Carolina Soul is a record seller based in Durham, NC, USA. They specialize in rare and classic soul, boogie, gospel and modern obscure tracks from the Carolinas and beyond, mixed with all-time bangers and ballads.
This program is curated by Ondas Representative, Dubby. It features artists, both well-known and unknown, with a unique aesthetic from a wide range of genres that used to be available at Ondas.
Michigan selector Shells plays 45s.
Neil Krug is an American visual artist, director, and photographer based in Los Angeles. Tune in for a sonic lysergic tale of love, heartbreak, and redemption.

An hour a month from LA label Total Stasis, responsible for releases by Ramzi, Aquarian Foundation, Anom Vitruv, Elysia Crampton, Bobo Eyes & Plush Throw, CS + Kreme, Fmvee, Second Language, Regularfantasy, Private Lesson, Alexi Baris, Laila Sakini, and Sebastiano Carghini.

Transmissions from the Outer Rim/Inner Edge.
“you know the gates themselves are made of flood.”
-Nadia Marcus
A monthly, eclectic road-trip exploring old landmarks and new terrain.

subtle.d: Sessions w/ Amy B is an underground multi-genre music show, showcasing the most prolific guests from all corners of the music industry.

Originally linking up in Wellington and playing shows with the Breaking Beats crew, Swampman and Zero Crumbs have reunited – bringing their smooth mixing and flexible selections to East London. 

In their monthly show, the pair explore the deep, dark, and soulful ends of DNB. Expect fresh underground tunes, deep cut classics, and a bit of banter in Kiwi accents.

subtle.n: THE CULTURE HEAD w/ SAINT VOX

subtle.d: Hailing from south london, pinkxbrains makes mixes referencing breakbeat and happy hardcore inspired by oldskool british dance music, connecting this to bits of gabber, drum n bass, techstep and even speedcore every now and then. Her sets are a silly and brutal spin on the hardcore tradition.
Hailing from Belfast but making moves in Nottingham, Nikki O is a DJ and radio presenter whose sets blend 4/4 rhythms, breakbeats, and the bassier side of techno.

subtle.n: House Plants Dont Like House Music

subtle.d:
DJ & Producer, B-Say has been a Subtle resident DJ for over 3 years.

His radio shows tend to focus on the 140 bass music scene and aims to showcase unreleased/forthcoming music from upcoming artists, as well as premiering his own unreleased material. 

More recently B-Say has ventured out from solely DJ'ing Dubstep, with his bi-monthly 'Dub & Steppers Show' which he uses to premier his own productions.

Slick is a London-based Producer and DJ combining the sounds of Grime and Drill.
Expect sets to span from sparse wave and weightless to classic NY and UK Drill, with everything in between
J:KENZO is a producer and record label owner (Artikal Music & Lion Charge) from the UK. Known for his minimalistic dark tribal sound in the both the dubstep and drum and bass scenes since 2006.

subtle.n: Pattern Recognition w/ R A L L Y
Mid Morning Matters w/ Alfie Danger
Taking the Peel w/ Badly Drawn Banana

subtle.d:
DJ and radio producer TILDA will be live from the studio to kick off your weekend. She’ll cover all corners of electronic music as well as showcasing unmissable new tracks & chatting about motives for the weekend. 

Each month TILDA will be closing the show with a signature mix.

Live & Direct is the show that promises to make you dance and make you laugh, with your fave tunes that make you go 'Rahhh ain't hear this in time' and all the cheesy jokes from me, Hannah :) Lock in for the sickest guests and the most relatable stories about daily slips and hilarious situations I find myself in.

Following his widely acclaimed breakout moment winning the 2013 DMC World Online Championships, Jon1st quickly built an international reputation as a ‘DJ’s DJ’. Not only proving himself as one of the world’s most diverse and musical turntablists, Jon also established himself as an on the pulse club DJ mixing across the alternative bass music spectrum and as an in demand live performer around the world, as well as recording acclaimed guest mixes for everyone from DJ Mag to Boiler Room to Ninja Tune’s Solid Steel to Mary Anne Hobbs to Keep Hush.

Established in 2013, eatmybeat is a hybrid record label & club brand that was brought together by a group of friends with a passion for electronic music and building community. With diverse tastes, they support and champion the underground bass music scene through events and releases on the label. Refusing to be pigeonholed into a specific sound, they showcase everything from hip-hop, bass & breaks, through to techno, jungle, dubstep and grime. As long as it's tasty and full fat, you best believe eatmybeat are snacking on it.

Born and bred in Hackney, East London. SK’s influences include Rare Groove, Motown, Hip Hop, Soul, RnB, Reggae and Lovers Rock, he first started DJ’ing in 1992 on the Hardcore/Jungle scene under the name of DJ Slick making a number of appearances on the pirate radio scene and producing a number of underground white-label beats.
Born in Sunderland, based in London, Kitschko's productions and selections display a deep appreciation of UK club culture, and an affinity for late night, introspective sounds.

As a drummer since childhood, Chacho has always had an insatiable appetite for new and unique beats.
Combining his love of global percussion, dark grooves and deeper low end frequencies, 
his sets feature a blend of dubstep, grime, garage, breaks, hip hop and other flavours from around the world.

ixxi and Fei take you on a percussive journey with their show syncop8, moving from downtempo ambient to breaks, polyrhythms, and high energy beats, exploring every rhythmic and textural nuance in between.
Representing UK Bass Music Culture across a range of styles, sounds and tempos.

Rolling through varied tempo's and genres, Jimmy 2 Shoes brings dance floor orientated vibes and flows to wriggle your toes to. Expect eclectic selections and the freshest sounds from the UK underground.

As if kid is a professional Producer, DJ and Drummer from the west country (UK). Real name "Sid", He is versatile in producing hot records in various genres: Grime, UK Drill, Hip Hop, Jungle and more with an ever-growing number of global commercial placements and releases. He regularly collaborates with DJ Slimzee under alias E3 Breaks and with DJ Raggs under the alias Slamfire!

subtle.n: The Wheel Up Show w/ Tripta
subtle.d: Tripta is a Toronto based producer/DJ focusing on the darker sounds of Grime. Also blending elements of Drill, Dubstep and even Jungle all together for a unique sound you won't hear anywhere else. Signed to Slimzee's 'Slimzo's Recordings' and ‘Rotpot Records’.

Sound Arkitek is a Chicago hip-hop DJ with a love for all things drum & bass. 

With over 20 years experience playing house parties, raves, clubs and bars he has an encyclopedic knowledge of music but has always been a participant in jungle culture. In the early 2000s he was exposed to the genre primarily through Dieselboy and Danny The Wildchild mixes as well as the “Jungle Book” series of mixtapes. He became obsessed after hearing Bad Company’s “The Nine” and “Four Days,” as well as Pendulum’s “Vault.” 

As time went on, he got deeper into the scene, going to raves while buying records and posting on Drum & Bass Arena and DNBForum before turning 21 at which point he began going to Lava Lounge for Bass By The Pound’s “Seminar” series. The first legal drum & bass party he attended was Chase & Status at the aforementioned Lava Lounge, and he will never forget the energy when the duo played DJ Hazard’s “Killers Don’t Die” and it got a rewind. His love for the scene led to him playing drum & bass parties, opening for artists like Original Sin, Gridlok, and LTJ Bukem among others. 

His Subtle Radio show is an hour of the finest tunes in the scene at the moment. 

To keep up, follow @djsoundarkitek on Instagram!

Darcy is 23 year old DJ from Bristol who specialises in dubstep and grime. With a love for choppy techniques and old school grime cyphers, her sounds create a unique energy that reflect in her sets and mixes. 

New to the scene, she has played alongside 140 legends like Just Jane, White Peach Records, Riz la Teef and more. Working closely with underground labels like Partum Audio, as well as curating a montly show for her residency on Mondo Radio- Darcy continues to develop her style and make her name.

subtle.n: Odds and Ends w/ Moon J

subtle.d: Dubversified showcases Canadian West Coast DJ talent specializing in Bass Music. Hosted by Mirage, founder of Dubversified Culture, a community-led organization focusing on music, art, and events. Mirage, originally from Québec, blends house and hip-hop since 2010, now exploring 140bpm and Deep D&B.

subtle.n: Into The Lion's Den w/ Restrikt

subtle.d: Potent Funk records’ Matt Frost - Well known for his technical abilities and Sleazy bass music style, Frost covers all angles from UK alt Rap to the LA beat scene.

Get ready to embark on a captivating sonic journey of underground music with Charlie Kelly. Including new and timeless sounds from the depths of rap, drill, grime, and experimental genres from the vibrant streets of the UK and beyond. Charlie unearths the very best in music that pushes boundaries. Off the mic, Charlie is a Radio Producer and Social Media Executive with an eclectic music taste spanning across many different cultures, decades, and styles. Hailing from North London with a love for audio and pop culture, you can expect to hear tune after tune when you’re locked into Charlie Kelly on Subtle.
BirdE brings an hour of the freshest Drum and Bass covering everything from liquid to techy steppers - the deeper the better.

casual_observer is a DJ and producer originally hailing from Amsterdam, where he co-organises the "moving closer" event series with friend and collaborator Bcl-2. He currently resides in Berlin. Starting his musical journey as a drummer, his music retains a heavy focus on groove, rhythm and experimentation.  Sets played by casual_observer are diverse and surprising, moving effortlessly between jungle, breaks, bass, footwork, and more. No matter the genre, his selection is sure to keep you on your toes!

In:flux Audio are a record label based in Leeds, UK founded by production duo Tik&Borrow. Since the label's inception in October 2013, they have dabbled in multiple dance music styles with the emphasis always being on the tracks being unique, and packed full of bass. Today the primary output for the label is from their Dubstep roster and this is focus of their show on Subtle - giving the artists and remixers chance to showcase their sounds with an hour guest mix, all hosted by label bossman Tik.

I’m a 19 year old DJ and producer from Newcastle upon Tyne, mainly playing and producing music around the 140bpm mark. I started out playing old 2-step and jungle records, before moving my focus to mainly dubstep and grime. Along with my friends Pirata and White Label, I run Newcastle’s only current 140 night, Well Irie.

subtle.n: THE CULTURE HEAD w. SAINT VOX

subtle.d: DIGDIS presents a selection of tracks that captures the vibrant and ever-evolving edges of dance music. Each show features a wide range of music that can be enjoyed both on the dancefloor and in more intimate listening spaces.

My show focuses on percussive, club sounds, taking inspiration from the edges of drill, funky and bass music. In both my mixes and productions, I like to keep the energy high and a little whimsical. Expect some moments of ambient and R&B too, just so we can all catch our breath.
With a monthly show on Subtle, Niceup is a London based DJ with a unique style. Pushing UKG, Breakbeat, Bass, Electro and 140. Weaving through genres showcasing new releases and older cuts.

Jedah started DJ'ing at the tender age of 18 years of age specialising in UK Garage/Grime. 

Jedah is currently the DJ for Grime Original Hollowman Jendor of the former Grime Collective Essentials/ OG's.

Responsible for “that massive grime tune with the Psycho strings”, UK producers/DJs Trends & Boylan are well versed in what the scene has to offer. They use this platform to showcase music from across the 140 spectrum from Grime to Dubstep. Anything goes!!

XOSÉ is a DJ and aspiring producer mixing and making mostly UK Garage, Grime and UK Funky. FORWARD PRESSURE largely focuses on the aforementioned UK born genres, though you can expect a variety of UK influenced sounds.

Sempra is a producer & DJ based in London, specialising in the fusion of UK Garage, Jungle and Breakbeat with dreamy vocal melodies and the beautiful instrumentation found in Soul and contemporary RnB. Sempra’s consistent output has been released by labels such as Future Classic and Headroom, gaining industry support from the likes of Nia Archives, Sherelle, Yung Singh and Dr Dubplate.

Cicely is a northern raised London based music photographer and DJ. From learning to mix during lockdown, she has since played at clubs across the country in venues such as Fabric, Corsica and Fold.

Cicely runs a collective and events night under the name NRG CRU which focus heavily on the high energy rave sound. She is highly influenced by the northern sound she grew up with, and you can hear this within her sets. Expect heavy blends of techno and hardcore while she shines the light on her favourite northern artists.

Live & Direct is the show that promises to make you dance and make you laugh, with your fave tunes that make you go 'Rahhh ain't hear this in time' and all the cheesy jokes from me, Hannah :) Lock in for the sickest guests and the most relatable stories about daily slips and hilarious situations I find myself in.

Bristol-born and London-based, Not Bad For A Girl resident DaiSu has been involved in the music scene since 2018 and has featured on stations such as Radio 1 Dance, BBC 6 Music and Melodic Distraction, as well as playing on line ups for Keep Hush, Skiddle and Red Bull. Her penchant for bass, breaks and 2-step has landed her gigs supporting acts such as Interplanetary Criminal, Main Phase, Craigie Knowes and Big Ang. In September 2022, her debut EP ‘Lightwork’ was released with Gather Records and was featured in DJ Mag's staff picks that same month.

Vinyl DJ from Leigh-on-Sea. Loves collecting records with a wide array of taste ranging from House and Techno to Grime, Dubstep and Jungle. Garage holds a special place in his heart and makes up the largest part of my collection and DJ sets.

DJ & Producer hailing from Watford influenced by Hip-Hop, Dubstep, Grime with releases on NSX records & Ghost Phone, spinning electronic genres from R&B edits, Drum and Bass and everything in between.
Highlander brings you 2 hours of the freshest Jungle, Hardcore, Dubstep and Breaks. 3rd Saturday 7-9pm lock in!

subtle.n: What's The Weather, Selecta? w/ Megan Wroe

subtle.d:
Hailing from Mumbai, now living in London, Chaitu is energised by the UK sound and scene.

With a love of all things weird, weighty and groovy; his mixes and productions bridge electro, techno, breaks, UKG and Jungle, with sprinklings of everything in between.

Chaitu champions provocative beats that break down the barriers of style, genre and expectation, all while keeping you moving.

Saraphim (aka RNS & RDubz) are two Essex based Producer/DJ’s currently focused on Dubstep & the 140 spectrum, mixing ethnical and grime influences into their music. You can expect anything from deep and melodic meditative vibes to high energy driven music.
London based DJ who enjoys exploring the darker, bassier corners of Jungle, Breaks, Techno and Drum & Bass, especially when it is laced with a bit of acid.

Wheel2Wheel is a Manchester based event which primarily focuses on the underground sectors to genres such as UK Garage, House, Tech House, Electro, Minimal and Breakbeat. Co-Founder Freddie SJ hosts the first hour of the show, sharing his favourites as well as recent digs across the genres, and then invites fellow friends, artists and nights from the scene to present hour-long guest mixes which aims to shine a light on their sound and who they are!


With hours of Discogs screen-time under his belt and a passion for 90's & early 00's releases, expect to hear a variety of different tunes from Labels you may have never heard of and Countries you might not expect!


Give us a follow on Instagram to hear about our upcoming events and all other things music related! @wheel2wheel.mcr

subtle.d: Japanese DJ from Tokyo, currently living in London.  Based on UK club music, but straddles other genres such as dancehall, reggaeton, gqom and amapiano.

Hailing from northern Italy, STANDARD is a collective of artists, DJs and producers that aims at the promotion of bass music: Garage, UK Funky, Breaks, Leftfield Bass, Leftfield Techno, Dubstep, everything in between and beyond. They focus on the Italian Bass scene, showcasing new up-and-coming artists as well as established talents from all over the peninsula.

Oddkut is a producer & DJ hailing from Balakovo City, Russia. He's part of the Russian collective "United Gang" who are a Moscow-based community of local musicians, DJ's and promoters teamed up by their genuine love & interest in UK underground music, "TAЭT VREMYA" art group and the creator of the Moscow parties "Judder".
"The calm before summer"

Kishan is a DJ and Producer currently based in London. Actively involved in the music scene already, he produces and mixes a wide range of genres including UK Garage, Drum & Bass, House, Disco and Afrobeat.

Midlands born, London based producer and DJ influenced by UK funky, broken techno, garage and early dubstep. 

Has released on Keysound recordings, RKS, eatmybeat, ec2a, Durkle Disco and Dimsum records

2Step Selects is a monthly show hosted by the Choki Biki Records crew. Founded in Dublin, Ireland, CBR consists of DJ Sharpson, 2step.png, Frame Shift, and MICK. The show consists of an all round breaks, electro, ukg and jungle hour, followed by an Irish showcase, demonstrating all the best Ireland has to offer collective/party/Dj & Producer wise!

More recently B-Say has ventured out from solely DJ'ing Dubstep, with his bi-monthly 'Dub & Steppers Show' which he uses to premier his own productions.

Following his widely acclaimed breakout moment winning the 2013 DMC World Online Championships, Jon1st quickly built an international reputation as a ‘DJ’s DJ’. Not only proving himself as one of the world’s most diverse and musical turntablists, Jon also established himself as an on the pulse club DJ mixing across the alternative bass music spectrum and as an in demand live performer around the world, as well as recording acclaimed guest mixes for everyone from DJ Mag to Boiler Room to Ninja Tune’s Solid Steel to Mary Anne Hobbs to Keep Hush.

subtle.d: Established in 2013, eatmybeat is a hybrid record label & club brand that was brought together by a group of friends with a passion for electronic music and building community. With diverse tastes, they support and champion the underground bass music scene through events and releases on the label. Refusing to be pigeonholed into a specific sound, they showcase everything from hip-hop, bass & breaks, through to techno, jungle, dubstep and grime. As long as it's tasty and full fat, you best believe eatmybeat are snacking on it.
Born in Sunderland, based in London, Kitschko's productions and selections display a deep appreciation of UK club culture, and an affinity for late night, introspective sounds.

As a drummer since childhood, Chacho has always had an insatiable appetite for new and unique beats.
Combining his love of global percussion, dark grooves and deeper low end frequencies, 
his sets feature a blend of dubstep, grime, garage, breaks, hip hop and other flavours from around the world.
